job_history.work_description: Provides case management services including intake, assessment, crisis intervention, advocacy, referral, and monitoring of families. Gathers social history to assess family strengths, and weaknesses, and to assess existing problems. Conducts home visits and office base services, and accompanies consumers as needed.

Providing linkage and advocacy to children and adolescents and their families Assists families in developing the skills and supports necessary to enhance quality of life, increase adaptive functioning, and improve self-sufficiency in the community
Responsible for a variety of duties aimed at providing client services such as receiving, paying out, and keeping an accurate record of all monies involved in paying and receiving transactions.
